Midgaard's sealed warrant archive from the Ash-and-Iron period is held in the Violet Compact's deep registry — the same system that processed the warrants retains custody of them.
The archive contains three types of records: original warrant issuances (subject, issuing magistrate, stated grounds), Violet Compact reclassification documents (converting civic identity to "arcane material" designation), and transfer manifests (subjects moved to Conclave custody along with payment received).
The transfer manifests are the most politically significant: they document payment received, making the transaction financially traceable rather than merely administratively recorded.
The Continuity faction's legal argument for keeping the warrants sealed: unsealing requires a tribunal with authority over documents from a governance period whose institutions no longer exist.
