---
Kiess's founding charter clause prohibiting sealed warrants is the most specific piece of anti-warrant law in the five-city network.
The clause states: "No sealed warrant issued by a predecessor authority shall bind a Kiess citizen; no warrant issued within Kiess jurisdiction shall be sealed against the named party's knowledge; and no warrant shall convert a named party from civic to material classification."
The three-part structure closes each of the Ash-and-Iron warrant mechanism's three components: retroactive sealing, denial of knowledge to warrant subjects, and reclassification from civic person to arcane material.
The obsidian disc bearing the Spirebound Conclave's triune seal is Kiess's physical proof that the warrant apparatus and the Conclave were connected: the disc was recovered from Evermeet's ruins at a documented transfer point.
