Rakuen's founding population included people who arrived carrying sealed-warrant classifications from Midgaard's intake system.
The Garden Ledger's founding-generation records show dual-registry entries — Midgaard intake numbers alongside Rakuen registration numbers — corresponding to people processed through the emergency warrant system before being routed south.
Rakuen's political class has debated whether to formally petition for access to the sealed warrants corresponding to Garden Ledger founding-generation entries.
The Compact Purist faction opposes: seeking access acknowledges Midgaard's jurisdictional authority over Rakuen's founding population history.
The Assimilation League faction supports: Midgaard's institutional records are where the documentation is, and refusing to access them because of jurisdictional objections means accepting the sealed warrant's denial of history as a practical outcome.

