---
Ashborn are the population most directly harmed by Midgaard's sealed warrants from the Ash-and-Iron period.
The misclassification of Ashborn as a human subtype made them subject to human-debtor warrants — the same warrants authorizing condemned-debtor transfers to the Spirebound Conclave.
Ashborn oral tradition preserves accounts of individuals who arrived at Midgaard's intake yards, were registered under emergency warrants, and did not return.
The Conclave's Ember Canon program — theorizing fire as the most fundamental transformative force — was motivated in part by observing early Ashborn and attempting to replicate volcanic transformation through fire ritual; it obtained experimental subjects partly through Midgaard's warrant system.
Ashborn communities' demand for the sealed warrants to be opened is simultaneously a demand for historical acknowledgment and a demand for the experimental record of what was done to their ancestors.
