Rivennid custodial networks in the delta settlements during the Ash-and-Iron period maintained parallel records of population movements that the official sealed warrant system specifically obscured.
The Rivennid practice of tracking who passed through their custodial nodes meant that some transfer-period movement was recorded in Rivennid network logs even when warrant sealing removed the same movement from official registries.
The operational records document people as supply needs (food quantities, shelter requirements, medical status) — a different data format but useful for cross-referencing warrant-period population movements.
Kowloon's Reckoning faction has proposed cross-referencing Rivennid custodial logs against Black Ledger period records to reconstruct transfer sequences; Rivennid network elders have not declined but have not confirmed willingness to provide access.
